We treat the weighted graph as a Markov chain. In this context, the probability measure μj attached to node j ∈ V can be thought of as the probability of a 1-step random walk starting from node j. The 1-step transition probability pjk of going from j to k is expressed by the principle of mass action39. According to this principle, if there is a known connection between gene j and gene k (i.e., (j, k) ∈ E), then the probability that they interact is proportional to the product of their CN values:3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
