				\begin{document}$${{\Delta }}S\times {{\Delta }}R.$$\end{document}ΔS×ΔR.Here, robustness refers to the ability of a system to recover or maintain its ability to function after it is perturbed in some way (e.g., stress signal). The OR curvature on networks is directly derived from the Lott–Sturm–Villani relationship, and thus was chosen over other possible discrete models43–46.

